---
# Claude Memory Manager - User Configuration
# Copy this file to .claude/claude-memory-manager.local.md and customize

# Search Configuration
defaultSearchMode: semantic  # Options: semantic, text, both
# semantic: Use vector embeddings for similarity search
# text: Use keyword/regex search
# both: Combine both approaches

# Auto-Indexing Settings
autoIndex:
  enabled: true
  batch_size: 3  # Conversations per batch
  min_content_length: 20  # Minimum words for indexing
  max_content_length: 5000  # Maximum tokens (summary fallback)

# Embedding Configuration
embedding:
  model: claude-sonnet-4-6  # Model for generating embeddings
  dimensions: 1536  # Vector dimensions
  index_conversations: true  # Index conversations with embeddings

# Database Settings
database:
  path: ~/.claude/memory/memory.db
  max_size_mb: 500  # Trigger cleanup when exceeded
  backup_enabled: true
  backup_path: ~/.claude/memory/backups

# Retention Policy
retention:
  conversations_days: 365  # Keep conversations for N days
  unindexed_days: 90  # Keep unindexed for N days
  keep_tagged: true  # Never remove tagged conversations

# Cleanup Settings
cleanup:
  enabled: true
  schedule: weekly  # Options: weekly, monthly, manual
  day: sunday  # Day of week for weekly cleanup
  prune_old: true
  rebuild_indexes: true
  optimize_storage: true

# Indexing Triggers
indexingTriggers:
  session_end: true  # Index after session ends
  summary_update: true  # Re-index when summary changes
  explicit_request: true  # Index when user requests

# Performance Settings
performance:
  async_operations: true  # Run indexing in background
  max_concurrent_requests: 3
  timeout_seconds: 30
  retry_attempts: 3
  retry_delay_ms: 1000

# Logging
logging:
  enabled: true
  level: info  # Options: debug, info, warn, error
  path: ~/.claude/memory/memory.log

# Advanced Settings
advanced:
  enable_fts_search: true  # Full-text search support
  vector_distance_function: cosine  # Options: cosine, euclidean, dot
  embedding_cache_enabled: true
---

# Claude Memory Manager Configuration Guide

## Quick Start

1. Copy this file: `cp .claude/claude-memory-manager.local.md.example .claude/claude-memory-manager.local.md`
2. Edit the values below to customize behavior
3. Settings are loaded automatically on plugin start

## Configuration Sections

### Search Configuration

`defaultSearchMode`: Determines default search behavior when user queries memory
- `semantic`: Search by meaning using vector embeddings (recommended)
- `text`: Search by keywords/regex matching
- `both`: Combine semantic and text search for comprehensive results

### Auto-Indexing Settings

Control how and when conversations are indexed with embeddings:

- `enabled`: Enable/disable automatic indexing
- `batch_size`: Number of conversations to process per batch
- `min_content_length`: Minimum word count to consider for indexing
- `max_content_length`: Maximum tokens to embed (fallback to summary if exceeded)

### Embedding Configuration

Settings for vector embedding generation:

- `model`: Claude model used for generating embeddings
- `dimensions`: Size of vector representation (affects search quality)
- `index_conversations`: Whether to create vector similarity index

### Database Settings

Storage and database management:

- `path`: Location of SQLite database file
- `max_size_mb`: Size threshold that triggers cleanup
- `backup_enabled`: Automatic backup before destructive operations
- `backup_path`: Directory for backup files

### Retention Policy

How long to keep conversation data:

- `conversations_days`: Maximum age to retain conversations
- `unindexed_days`: Maximum age for conversations without embeddings
- `keep_tagged`: Never delete conversations that have tags

### Cleanup Settings

Periodic database maintenance:

- `enabled`: Enable automatic cleanup operations
- `schedule`: When to run cleanup (weekly/monthly/manual)
- `day`: Day of week for weekly cleanup
- `prune_old`: Remove old conversations per retention policy
- `rebuild_indexes`: Rebuild database indexes for performance
- `optimize_storage`: Compact database to reclaim space

### Indexing Triggers

When to trigger indexing:

- `session_end`: Index conversation after session completes
- `summary_update`: Regenerate embedding when summary changes
- `explicit_request`: Index when user explicitly requests

### Performance Settings

Tune indexing and search performance:

- `async_operations`: Run indexing in background (non-blocking)
- `max_concurrent_requests`: Limit concurrent embedding requests
- `timeout_seconds`: Maximum time for indexing operations
- `retry_attempts`: Number of retries on transient errors
- `retry_delay_ms`: Delay between retries (exponential backoff)

### Logging

Control logging verbosity:

- `enabled`: Enable logging to file
- `level`: Log verbosity (debug/info/warn/error)
- `path`: Location of log file

### Advanced Settings

Expert-level configuration:

- `enable_fts_search`: Full-text search support
- `vector_distance_function`: Similarity metric for vectors
- `embedding_cache_enabled`: Cache embedding results
- `custom_prompt`: Custom prompt for embedding generation

## Example Configurations

### Minimal Configuration

```yaml
autoIndex:
  enabled: true

retention:
  conversations_days: 90
```

### Development Configuration

```yaml
autoIndex:
  enabled: true
  batch_size: 1

logging:
  enabled: true
  level: debug
```

### Production Configuration

```yaml
defaultSearchMode: semantic
autoIndex:
  enabled: true
  batch_size: 5

cleanup:
  enabled: true
  schedule: weekly

performance:
  async_operations: true
  max_concurrent_requests: 5
```

## Notes

- All paths support `~` expansion for home directory
- Settings are reloaded on plugin start (restart required)
- Boolean values: `true` or `false`
- Numbers: Use integers or floats as appropriate
- Strings: Use quotes for all string values
